üìÑ DigiArsenal Submission Guidelines

Welcome to the DigiArsenal Research Repository. This document explains how to submit bugs, update requests, and program contributions in a structured, auditable, and traceable way.

1Ô∏è‚É£ General Principles

Core-Docs/ is immutable: do not attempt direct edits.

All submissions must go through Issues using the provided templates.

Attachments are uploaded via the Issue editor (drag & drop).

All submissions must include Author / Reporter Name for proper attribution.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Submission Types
A. Bug Report

Use this template to report defects, inconsistencies, or technical issues.

Required fields:

Author / Reporter Name

Description of the bug

Optional file attachments (logs, screenshots, reproducible artifacts)

Steps:

Go to Issues ‚Üí New Issue ‚Üí Bug Report

Fill in all fields and attach relevant files

Submit

After submission: The team will review, label, and track your report.

B. Update Request

Use this template to propose feature enhancements, conceptual improvements, or documentation updates.

Required fields:

Author / Reporter Name

Request details

Optional supporting files (diagrams, references)

Steps:

Go to Issues ‚Üí New Issue ‚Üí Update Request

Fill in all fields and attach optional files

Submit

After submission: The team evaluates feasibility and relevance.

C. Program Submission

Use this template to submit programs, scripts, or code artifacts for review and inclusion.

Required fields:

Author / Reporter Name

Program description

Upload program files (ZIP, source code, documentation)

Steps:

Go to Issues ‚Üí New Issue ‚Üí Program Submission

Fill in all fields

Drag & drop program files in the attachment section

Submit

After submission: The team reviews, and approved submissions may be archived in the Programs/ folder.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Review & Archival Process

All submissions are reviewed for clarity, validity, and relevance.

Approved submissions are manually moved to the corresponding folder:

Programs/ ‚Üí approved program files

Update-Requests/ ‚Üí archive of approved feature requests

Bug-Reports/ ‚Üí archive of resolved bugs (optional)

Each commit references the original issue number for traceability.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Submission Best Practices

Be clear and concise in descriptions

Include all relevant files in attachments

Use your real name or a consistent identifier in Author field

Avoid submitting the same issue multiple times
